summary: Jason Reynold’s Miles Morales: Spider-Man:  Is literally about Miles Morales on an introspective level and his life as a...
body:
Jason Reynold’s Miles Morales: Spider-Man:  Is literally about Miles Morales on an introspective level and his life as a superhero. It’s author is Black, authenticity is felt throughout. It’s a Young Adult Novel.

Marvel’s Spider-Man: Explicitly positions Peter Parker as the protagonist of the narrative completely his own, makes clear Miles Morales is a supporting character in his narrative. It doesn’t use Miles’ narrative for Peter.

Into the Spiderverse: Promotes itself as a “Miles-centric movie” following Spider-Man: Homecoming backlash, when it’s really Yet Another Spider-Man Crossover Event Thing™ using Miles Morales as a selling point. It’s an Animated Movie by Sony.
